These are pertinent questions. I didn't go in much detail in description because I thought that it would detract too much from the main concept.

People at the current site don't know what is in the room. All on-site documentation on 964 is fabricated and says that it can walk through walls, bend steel, blow the heads with its thought and is memetic Japanese schoolgirl. So as long as 964 is none of those things everything should be fine.

If they hear an elephant in the containment chamber, it won't trigger reconstruction because this information is not sufficient to describe 964. As long as this elephant can't talk.

 is actually quite big. Digital data at 200km mark will trigger reconstruction ~2 weeks after it's created.

Regarding long term-memory, protocol 964Δ6h takes care of that. I imagine it to be a nastier variation of amnesiacs, that not so much 'erases' as 'scrambles' memories, so that 964 will have to spend another month detecting them. Also, human memory is quite complex. Even if you walk into containment chamber and stare directly at 964, it will probably take around a hour before reconstruction starts. For comparison, written text from this distance will trigger it in under a minute.

Furthermore keep in mind that all this containment procedures and protocols a far from perfect. Despite all Foundation efforts new reconstruction occurs at least every two weeks, usually more often.

And it's okay to be confused. I wrote it, and I am still a little confused too.







